## Infloww: Scripts vs Sequences
- **Script** = single standalone message, chatter picks manually
- **Sequence** = chain of scripts, first triggers auto-queue of next
- Rule of thumb: If chatter needs to READ response → standalone. If 2+ messages regardless of response → sequence.
- Journey (R → TB → S → AC) = ONE sequence
- OBJ handling = standalone scripts (chatter evaluates response)

## TPDs Selling Method (Custom Content)
- T = Teasing (build excitement first)
- P = Price (drop price while fan is excited)
- Ds = Distraction Shift (immediately ask a question to redirect attention from price)
- ALWAYS collect payment BEFORE making the custom

## Dating App Traffic — Meetup Redirect Module
